    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A stick, used with a frame loom, to which every other thread of the warp is attached. The heddle rod can either be lifted away from the frame loom to open the shed, or it holds one shed still while a shed stick is moved to create the shed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000132/Suzzallo-UW</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050842/Broudy, The Book of Looms (1979)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用於框織機的粗棍，每隔一條的經紗可連接於其上。藉著將綜線桿拉離框織機而打開梭道，或在移動隔棒以產生梭道時，固定住另一個梭口。 用於框織機的粗棍，每隔一條的經紗可連接於其上。藉著將綜線桿拉離框織機而打開梭道，或在移動隔棒以產生梭道時，固定住另一個梭口。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
